def_en: The Normans were the people who came from northern France and took control of England in 1066, or their descendants.

def_cn: 诺曼时期的;(尤指建筑风格)诺曼式的
def_en: Norman is used to refer to the period of history in Britain from 1066 until around 1300, and in particular to the style of architecture of that period.
